  <reg:acttitle>Forest Act</reg:acttitle>
  <reg:title>Timber Definition Regulation</reg:title>
  <reg:amsincluded>[includes amendments up to B.C. Reg. 393/97]</reg:amsincluded>
  <reg:content>
    <bcl:section id="d2e27" toc="false">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Definition</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>In this regulation, <in:term>timber</in:term> includes all special forest products
        designated from time to time by regulation under the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96157_00" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Forest
          Act</in:doc></bcl:link>.</bcl:text>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e45">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Application of definition</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>The expanded meaning of "timber" applies to the following provisions:</bcl:text>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d2e56">
        <bcl:num>a</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>the definitions "Crown timber" and "timber processing facility" in section 1 of
          the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96157_00" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Forest Act</in:doc></bcl:link>;</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d2e68">
        <bcl:num>b</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>sections 5, 8, 14, 15, 23, 24, 30, 35, 45, 48, 49, 51, 57, 64, 70, 75, 84, 85, 89,
          93, 94 (2), (4) and (5), 96 to 99, 103 to 105, 108, 110, 114, 117, 118, 120, 121, 128,
          129, 131, 134, 136, 143 and 163 (b), (d) and (e) of the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96157_00" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Forest
            Act</in:doc></bcl:link>.</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:hnote>[am. B.C. Reg.393/97, s. 5.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <reg:provisionsnote>[Provisions of the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96157_00" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Forest
        Act</in:doc></bcl:link>, R.S.B.C. 1997, c. 157, relevant to the enactment of this
      regulation: section 151
        (3)]</reg:provisionsnote>
  </reg:content>
</reg:regulation>